# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in your values. .env.local also works
# — Vite reads both. Vite only exposes vars prefixed with VITE_ to client
# code; non-prefixed vars are silently ignored.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REQUIRED for Chrome builds — build fails fast if missing.
# Optional for `npm run build:safari`.
#
# Macify CDN base URL. Single host that serves both:
#   - GET <BASE>/itunes-assets/...     → reverse proxy to sylvan.apple.com
#   - GET <BASE>/music/musicNNNNN.mp3  → R2 bucket of zen-mode music
#
# Set up: deploy cloudflare-worker/worker.js to a Worker route on
#   <BASE>/itunes-assets/*, and bind your music R2 bucket to <BASE>.
# No trailing slash.
#
# VITE_MACIFY_BASE=https://your-host.example.com

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTIONAL — only needed if you've also set up the matching Cloudflare
# firewall rule (see README "Building from source").
#
# Apple proxy access token. When set, appended to every video request as
# ?k=<token>; the firewall rule on <BASE>/itunes-assets/* drops callers
# that don't include it. Token is build-time inlined (visible in the
# published bundle) so it only filters casual abuse, not motivated
# attackers. Rotate by changing this value AND the firewall rule together.
#
# Generate:  openssl rand -hex 16
#
# VITE_APPLE_PROXY_KEY=your_random_hex_token

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPTIONAL — defaults to 7 days when unset.
#
# Donate prompt interval (milliseconds). Lower it for testing.
#   10000      -> 10 seconds
#   60000      -> 1 minute
#   3600000    -> 1 hour
#   86400000   -> 1 day
#   604800000  -> 7 days (production default)
#
# VITE_DONATE_INTERVAL_MS=60000
